The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 Business Briefs

 Chennai, Sept. 7: The United Forum of Bank Unions, a body of nine bank unions, has announced a nation-wide strike on September 12 after recent talks with the chief labour commissioner over the implementation of a memorandum of understanding failed. According to a release from C.H. Venkatachalam, general secretary of the All India Bank Employees Association, the unions will hold demonstrations before the banks in all centres on September 11.

 Dalian, Sept. 7: Sterling Biotech has acquired a Chinese company as a part of its effort to enhance its global footprint, a senior company executive said here today. Chairman and managing director Nitin J. Sandesara said the company was located near Beijing. 

 Mumbai, Sept. 7: Fortis Healthcare will acquire a 53.10 per cent stake in Chennai-based Malar Hospitals for an undisclosed amount. International Hospital, a wholly owned subsidiary of Fortis Healthcare together with Oscar Investments, has entered into an agreement regarding the acquisition.

 Mumbai, Sept. 7: The countrys foreign exchange reserves were a little lower by $2 million at $228.847 billion for the week ended August 31. The reserves had increased by $2.404 billion a week before to $228.849 billion after declining for two consecutive weeks.




